We recommended that management should see to it that Gender and Development (GAD) Plan of the agency will fully address and adhere to the basic purpose and objectives towards the role of women in becoming a participative partner in nation building and development, with the end view of protecting their lives and rights and to live a modest life in a society.

Likewise, we recommended that the GAD Focal Person  shall be responsible for conducting gender mainstreaming or self-assessment particularly on the following areas:

Seeing to it that the municipality’s plans, programs, projects and activities are aligned to the Philippine Plan for GAD;

Monitoring the use of GAD funds for the purpose for which they have been appropriated;

Determining whether gender issues were addressed by GAD interventions in the municipality. 

We recommended that the GAD Focal Person submit the targets and accomplishments for the year 2015 and thereafter pursuant to Joint Circular No. 2004-1 dated April 5, 2004.

